  "prompt": "I just finished highschool. What should I do while waiting to get in to a university?",
  "response": "Here are some productive ways to spend your time before university:\n\n1. Personal Development\n- Learn a new skill online\n- Take free online courses\n- Learn a language\n- Practice coding or digital skills\n\n2. Work Experience\n- Get a part-time job\n- Do internships\n- Volunteer\n- Gain work experience in a field of interest\n\n3. Financial Preparation\n- Save money for university expenses\n- Research scholarships\n- Learn basic financial management\n\n4. Professional Development\n- Build a resume\n- Network with professionals\n- Create a LinkedIn profile\n- Attend career workshops\n\n5. Personal Growth\n- Travel if possible\n- Read books\n- Start a hobby\n- Exercise and focus on health\n- Learn time management skills\n\n6. Academic Preparation\n- Review subjects you'll study in university\n- Brush up on math or writing skills\n- Take preparatory courses\n- Study for placement tests\n\n7. Creative Projects\n- Start a blog\n- Create a portfolio\n- Learn a musical instrument\n- Develop a personal project\n\n8. Mental Health\n- Practice stress management\n- Develop healthy routines\n- Connect with friends and family\n- Prepare mentally for university transition\n\nChoose activities that align with your interests and future goals.",
